Broke with Expensive Taste is the debut studio album by American rapper Azealia Banks. It was originally scheduled to be released in September 2012 by Interscope Records and Polydor Records, although suffered from several delays and label conflicts which ultimately saw Banks excused from her recording contract. The project was ultimately released to online music stores in collaboration with Prospect Park on November 6, 2014 without prior confirmation.
